.
.

21:11.700 --> 21:13.800
Anything's fine.

21:13.825 --> 21:15.953
<i>Go bang your head against the wall</i>
[Yiddish]

21:18.100 --> 21:21.000
- Thank you...
- Hillary.

21:21.000 --> 21:23.900
That's an unusual name.

21:23.900 --> 21:29.300
It's German. It means,
she whose bosoms defy gravity.

21:32.200 --> 21:35.400
Pleased to meet you.
My name's Nick.

21:35.400 --> 21:38.400
Nick, what does that mean?

21:38.400 --> 21:41.600
Nothing. My dad thought of it
while he was shaving.

21:46.700 --> 21:50.400
Are you in some kind of trouble
with the police?

21:50.400 --> 21:53.100
Some things are better left unsaid.

21:54.100 --> 21:55.800
Like what?

21:55.800 --> 22:02.600
Sometimes when you blow your nose
into a tissue and put it in your purse.

22:02.600 --> 22:09.100
Then you reach for your lipstick, your hand
gushes into it, and it goes all over...

22:09.100 --> 22:11.600
You're right.
Some things are better left unsaid.

22:15.600 --> 22:17.600
Thank you very much.

22:18.800 --> 22:21.100
Ladies and gentlemen.

22:21.100 --> 22:26.700
We are fortunate to have with us tonight,
a singer, whose great talent

22:26.700 --> 22:30.700
is exceeded only by his devotion
to his country.

22:31.100 --> 22:34.100
He truly has the gift of song.

22:34.100 --> 22:36.300
A golden voice. Inspired talent and...

22:36.300 --> 22:39.400
Is there something wrong?

22:39.400 --> 22:41.800
I was afraid this might happen.

22:41.800 --> 22:46.800
General Streck of the High Command
is a most fervent admirer,

22:46.800 --> 22:50.300
and owns a complete set of his works.

22:50.300 --> 22:53.800
He is a very shy and gentle man,

22:53.800 --> 22:57.800
but perhaps we could persuade him
to sing for us.

22:58.100 --> 23:00.200
Shall we ask him?

23:04.600 --> 23:08.600
I better do what they want.
I promised my manager.

23:22.900 --> 23:24.800
Thank you, sir.

23:26.800 --> 23:29.600
Watch the change
in the second chorus.

23:29.600 --> 23:31.000
Oh, my God.
240.5
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:38,000
Wop-bop-a-loom-a-blop-bam-boom 
Tutti frutti, oh Rudy, etc...

26:06.400 --> 26:07.800
Cedric!

26:20.500 --> 26:24.100
- What have they done to you?
- It was a trap!

26:24.100 --> 26:27.900
They must have known
I was staying at the Howard Johnson's.

26:27.900 --> 26:31.100
- But who did this?
- Never mind about that.

26:31.100 --> 26:33.800
We've got to rescue your father
before it's too late.

26:33.800 --> 26:36.200
But what are we going to do?

26:36.200 --> 26:37.400
I was...

26:39.400 --> 26:42.300
...supposed to go to the ballet tonight,

26:42.300 --> 26:45.200
to meet a man called "The Torch".

26:45.200 --> 26:46.900
Thank you.

26:46.900 --> 26:50.700
He's the leader of the Resistance.
He'll help us find your father.

26:50.700 --> 26:54.700
- I'll go.
- No, you can't go. It's too dangerous.

26:54.700 --> 26:57.600
I must! He'll be tortured.

26:57.600 --> 27:00.800
All right, but be very careful at the ballet.

27:00.800 --> 27:03.200
Where is the ticket?

27:03.200 --> 27:05.700
In the glove compartment.

27:05.700 --> 27:07.400
Can you reach it from the inside?

27:10.900 --> 27:13.300
How about the other hand?

27:17.600 --> 27:19.900
No, that's not it. Let me try.

27:24.700 --> 27:26.500
Here it is.

29:23.000 --> 29:25.700
Come on, we've got to get out of here.

29:25.700 --> 29:30.000
- Shouldn't we wait for the police?
- That was the police!

29:36.200 --> 29:38.100
In here.

29:46.800 --> 29:49.100
We can get out this way.

29:49.100 --> 29:53.000
- Wait. First you can explain.
- I'm not sure I can.

29:59.100 --> 30:01.600
I only know I have put you in great danger.

30:01.600 --> 30:03.800
Trust me. You must come with me.

30:03.800 --> 30:07.400
I don't know what trouble you're in,
but don't worry about me.

30:07.400 --> 30:10.400
I'm a guest of the government.
I can explain everything.

30:10.400 --> 30:13.000
But you're mistaken. They'll put you in...

30:14.900 --> 30:18.200
Go while you still can.
They can't do anything to me.

30:43.000 --> 30:49.300
Martin, boy am I glad to see you.
I've been here 20 minutes already.

30:51.900 --> 30:55.400
Nick, I've tried everything.

30:55.400 --> 30:58.800
The Embassy, the German Government,
the consulate.

30:58.800 --> 31:02.800
I even talked to the UN Ambassador.
It's no use.

31:03.100 --> 31:06.200
I just can't bring my wife to orgasm.

31:08.100 --> 31:11.000
That's a shame, Martin.

31:11.000 --> 31:13.200
Have you tried one of these?

31:17.500 --> 31:20.400
Thanks. I'll give it a whirl.

31:21.900 --> 31:27.600
I'm getting worried about this place.
I don't think they've even heard of a trial.

31:27.600 --> 31:31.000
All I know is, after you left the cafe
last night, I met a girl.

31:31.000 --> 31:33.600
Later at the ballet she was alone.

31:33.600 --> 31:36.400
Then I see this guy with a gun at her head.

31:36.400 --> 31:40.400
He's looking like he's gonna kill her
and might have if I hadn't stepped in.

31:40.800 --> 31:45.300
There's got to be someone you can call,
to straighten this mess out.

31:45.300 --> 31:49.300
I figure they've got to let you out
for your concert, Friday night.

31:49.600 --> 31:52.400
They're beaming it live by satellite
to 85 countries.

31:52.400 --> 31:57.000
Just relax and remember,
there's nothing to worry about.

32:02.897 --> 32:06.746
In domini patrum, spiritos
mortrium dios madre.

32:06.747 --> 32:10.416
Ominia, Gallias, Divisa
est en tres partes.

32:10.417 --> 32:13.287
Corpus dilecti. Quid pro quo.

32:13.288 --> 32:17.515
Veni vidi vici. No lo contendre.

32:17.516 --> 32:20.267
Habeas corpus. Rick Dureus.

32:20.268 --> 32:24.136
Ipzo facto. Pro forma pari passu.

32:24.137 --> 32:27.435
Hic hick hoc, huius, huius, huius.

32:27.436 --> 32:29.264
E Pluribus Unum.

32:29.406 --> 32:35.086
Oure-yay oing-gay oo-tay et-gay
ied-fray in the air-chay.

32:35.087 --> 32:38.055
Tempus fugit. Caveat emptor.

32:38.134 --> 32:40.213
Coitus interruptus.

32:40.214 --> 32:42.350
Mitzi Gaynor ad nauseum

32:42.400 --> 32:44.500
Amen.

32:53.100 --> 32:55.700
We wish to impress upon you, Mr. Rivers,

32:55.700 --> 32:59.500
that we have methods of dealing
with those who will not cooperate.

32:59.500 --> 33:03.500
For the last time,
why did you attack Sergeant Kruger?

33:03.900 --> 33:07.500
I didn't know who it was.
I just saw him pull a gun on a girl.

33:07.500 --> 33:13.300
Might I remind you, Mr. Rivers, the penalty
for murder is death by firing squad.

33:13.300 --> 33:17.300
Let us hope for your sake
that Sergeant Kruger survives.

33:21.700 --> 33:24.500
It is the hospital, mein General.

33:24.500 --> 33:28.500
What is the condition of Sergeant Kruger?

33:28.500 --> 33:34.600
I see. Let me know if there
is any change in his condition.

33:35.200 --> 33:37.100
He is dead.

33:41.900 --> 33:45.900
You leave me no alternative,
but to introduce two of my associates.

33:47.300 --> 33:51.300
Bruno is almost blind.
He has to operate wholly by touch.

33:52.800 --> 33:56.800
Klaus is a moron, who knows only what
he reads in "The New York Post".

33:57.100 --> 34:00.300
I believe they never let a man
lose consciousness

34:00.300 --> 34:02.600
however long they may work on him.

34:02.600 --> 34:04.600
You don't scare me.

34:04.600 --> 34:07.700
My manager is on his way
to the American Consulate.

34:07.700 --> 34:10.900
Do not be so sure, Mr. Rivers.

34:10.900 --> 34:13.100
Evidently, your friend did not realise

34:13.100 --> 34:16.900
that here in East Germany
we use 220 volt current.

34:16.900 --> 34:21.400
He was found in his hotel room impaled
on a large electrical device.

34:21.400 --> 34:23.600
Our surgeons did what they could

34:23.600 --> 34:28.400
but it took them two hours
just to get the smile off his face.

34:31.100 --> 34:34.199
Perhaps the American
has chosen to reconsider.

34:45.100 --> 34:48.800
Make sure they leave no marks.

34:51.904 --> 34:55.938
<i>Ich liebe Dich, mein Schatz.</i>
I love you, my darling

35:12.400 --> 35:16.100
Do you know which room
the final chemistry exam is in?

35:16.100 --> 35:19.400
All the exams are over.
Haven't you been to class?

35:19.400 --> 35:22.200
- No.
- But it's the end of the semester.

35:22.200 --> 35:28.300
No, I haven't studied.
Oh no, I'm back in school.

35:28.300 --> 35:31.300
I can't believe I'm back in school.

35:34.800 --> 35:36.300
Thank God.

35:41.400 --> 35:43.000
Well?

35:43.000 --> 35:46.300
They're still working on him.
He won't break.

35:46.300 --> 35:48.800
They've tried everything.

35:48.800 --> 35:51.600
Do you want me to bring out
the LeRoy Neiman paintings?

35:51.600 --> 35:55.600
No. We cannot risk violating
the Geneva Convention.

35:55.900 --> 35:58.100
We'll break him tomorrow.

37:17.300 --> 37:20.100
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

37:20.100 --> 37:23.900
My name is Nick Rivers.
Who are you?

37:23.900 --> 37:29.900
I am Dr Paul Flammond.
I am a prisoner here, just like you.

37:29.900 --> 37:33.500
A year ago, I was close to perfecting

37:33.500 --> 37:37.000
the first magnetic desalinisation process.

37:37.000 --> 37:41.000
So revolutionary,
it was capable of removing the salt

37:41.100 --> 37:44.800
from over 500 million gallons
of sea water a day.

37:44.800 --> 37:48.800
Do you realise what that could mean
to the starving nations of the earth?

37:51.100 --> 37:53.700
They'd have enough salt to last forever.

37:54.900 --> 37:57.800
But then one night,
the Secret Police broke into my house.

37:57.800 --> 38:01.200
They tore me from my family,
ransacked my laboratory

38:01.200 --> 38:04.000
and brought me to this dungeon.

38:04.000 --> 38:05.700
That sucks!

38:05.700 --> 38:08.600
For the first time in my life,

38:08.600 --> 38:13.100
- I am ashamed of being a scientist.
- What do you mean?

38:13.100 --> 38:17.100
They are forcing me to create
a horrible weapon.

38:17.200 --> 38:20.700
- Can't you refuse?
- I wish I could.

38:20.700 --> 38:23.700
But they are holding my daughter.

38:23.700 --> 38:28.200
They'll kill her unless I complete
the Polaris Mine by Sunday.

38:28.200 --> 38:31.700
Sunday? That's Simchas Torah.

38:31.700 --> 38:34.800
And the day the entire NATO
submarine fleet

38:34.800 --> 38:37.300
passes through the Straits of Gibraltar.

38:37.300 --> 38:39.600
Is this the Polaris mine?

38:39.600 --> 38:44.600
Yes. By Sunday I will be able to arm it
with a nuclear warhead.

38:44.600 --> 38:48.100
- How does it work?
- It is a magnetic mine

38:48.100 --> 38:52.700
so powerful it will attract itself
to submarines miles away.

38:52.700 --> 38:56.400
- How about that?
- Oh, no.

39:03.500 --> 39:07.500
Go quickly. If they find out
you've seen this, your life will be worth less

39:07.600 --> 39:10.800
than a truck load of dead rats
in a tampon factory.

39:20.300 --> 39:22.000
Right away.

39:22.000 --> 39:24.900
- Von Horst!
- Ja, mein General.

39:24.900 --> 39:28.000
The government wishes to avoid
an international incident.

39:28.000 --> 39:30.800
Mr. Rivers must perform
his concert tonight.

39:30.800 --> 39:33.700
He is to be executed this very minute.

39:33.700 --> 39:37.700
- It'll have to wait. Call them at once.
- Ja, mein General.

